{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-a013d9a179f4",
  "content": "ge `extract_rust_use` (line 246) to accept and use the module map:\n```rust\nfn extract_rust_use(\n    relations: &mut Vec<CodeRelation>,\n    source: &str,\n    node: &Node,\n    file_path: &str,\n    owner_idx: usize,\n    module_map: Option<&RustModuleMap>,\n) {\n    // ... inside each branch, replace:\n    //   resolve_rust_module_path(file_path, &path_text)\n    // with:\n    //   resolve_rust_module_path(file_path, &path_text, module_map)\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Rewrite `resolve_rust_module_path` to use the module map**\n\nReplace lines 410-422 in `treesitter.rs`:\n```rust\nfn resolve_rust_module_path(\n    file_path: &str,\n    module_path: &str,\n    module_map: Option<&RustModuleMap>,\n) -> String {\n    if module_path.starts_with(\"crate::\") || module_path.starts_with(\"super::\") || module_path == \"crate\" || module_path == \"super\" {\n        // Try module map first for accurate resolution\n        if let Some(map) = module_map {\n            if let Some(resolved) = map.resolve(file_path, module_path) {\n                return resolved;\n            }\n        }\n        // Fallback: record current file (old behavior)\n        file_path.to_string()\n    } else {\n        // External crate or std — try module map for workspace cross-crate refs\n        if let Some(map) = module_map {\n            if let Some(resolved) = map.resolve(file_path, module_path) {\n                return resolved;\n            }\n        }\n        // Unresolvable external — record module path as-is\n        module_path.to_string()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Update `GitAdapter::register_chunking` to build and pass the module map**\n\nIn `corvia-adapter-git/src/git.rs`, modify `register_chunking`:\n\nThe current trait signature `fn register_chunking(&self, registry: &mut FormatRegistry)` doesn't have access to the source path. We need to add a method to set the module map separately. Add to `GitAdapter`:\n\n```rust\nimpl GitAdapter {\n    pub fn new() -> Self {\n        Self { module_map: None }\n    }\n\n    /// Build and store the module map for a workspace root.\n    /// Call this before `register_chunking()`.\n    pub fn prepare(&mut self, workspace_root: &str) {\n        let path = Path::new(workspace_root);\n        let map = crate::module_resolver::RustModuleMap::build(path);\n        self.module_map = Some(std::sync::Arc::new(map));\n    }",
